# SECTION 1: Core Technical Definition & Intuitive Overview

## 1.1 Introduction to Scripting & JavaScript

**JavaScript** is a high-level, interpreted, multi-paradigm, dynamically-typed, prototype-based scripting language standardized under **ECMAScript (ES)** specification. It is the de-facto language of the **client-side web** and is also widely used on the server side (Node.js). In the KTU 2024 Scheme syllabus for Web Programming, JavaScript is positioned as the *behavior layer* of the web, complementing **HTML (structure)** and **CSS (presentation)**.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **KTU Definition (Board-Examiner Approved):** *‚ÄúJavaScript is a lightweight, interpreted scripting language used to create dynamic, interactive content in web browsers. It is executed by the browser's JavaScript engine (e.g., V8, SpiderMonkey) and provides object-oriented capabilities through prototypes rather than classical inheritance.‚Äù*

### Scripting Language vs Programming Language

| Aspect | Scripting Language | Programming Language |
|---|---|---|
| Execution | Interpreted (line-by-line) | Compiled (then executed) |
| Runtime | Needs host environment (browser/Node) | Standalone executables |
| Typing | Usually dynamic | Often static |
| Use Case | Glue, automation, web | System software, large apps |
| Speed | Slower (no compile-time optim) | Faster overall |

> [!NOTE]
> **Conceptual Analogy:** Think of HTML as the *skeleton* of a house, CSS as the *paint and decoration*, and JavaScript as the *electricity and plumbing* ‚Äî it makes the house *react*, *respond*, and *function*. A static page is like a photograph; a JavaScript-enabled page is like a short movie.

### Where JavaScript Fits in Web Architecture

- **HTML** ‚Üí Structure (semantic skeleton)
- **CSS** ‚Üí Presentation (look and feel)
- **JavaScript** ‚Üí Behavior (interactivity, logic, dynamic updates)

### Ways to Embed JavaScript

1. **Inline** ‚Äî inside an HTML attribute (e.g., `onclick="..."`)
2. **Internal** ‚Äî inside a `<script>` tag in the same HTML file
3. **External** ‚Äî inside a separate `.js` file linked via `<script src="app.js"></script>`

> [!TIP]
> The recommended KTU/industry practice is **External** scripts placed just before the closing `</body>` tag (or with `defer`/`async` attributes) for performance and maintainability.

## 1.2 Programming Fundamentals of JavaScript

### 1.2.1 Variables & Identifiers

A **variable** is a named memory location that stores a value. In modern ES6+ JavaScript, you declare variables using:

- `let` ‚Üí block-scoped, **re-assignable** (preferred for changing values)
- `const` ‚Üí block-scoped, **NOT re-assignable** (preferred for constants)
- `var` ‚Üí function-scoped, hoisted (legacy, avoid in modern code)

```javascript
let studentName = "Anand";   // can be re-assigned
const PI = 3.14159;          // cannot be re-assigned
var legacyVar = 10;          // function-scoped, hoisted
```

### 1.2.2 Data Types (Primitives & Reference)

JavaScript has **8 data types** in total ‚Äî 7 primitives and 1 reference type (Object).

| Type | Category | Example | Size Hint |
|---|---|---|---|
| `number` | Primitive | `42`, `3.14` | IEEE-754 (64-bit) double |
| `string` | Primitive | `"Kerala"` | UTF-16 sequence |
| `boolean` | Primitive | `true`, `false` | 1 bit logical |
| `null` | Primitive | `null` | intentional absence |
| `undefined` | Primitive | `undefined` | uninitialized |
| `bigint` | Primitive | `9007199254740993n` | arbitrary precision integer |
| `symbol` | Primitive | `Symbol("id")` | unique identifier |
| `object` | Reference | `{ }`, `[ ]`, `function` | heap-allocated |

> [!WARNING]
> `typeof null === "object"` is a **known bug** preserved for backward compatibility (since 1995). Examiners love this trick question!

### 1.2.3 Comments

```javascript
// single-line comment
/* multi-line
   block comment */
```

### 1.2.4 Statements and Strict Mode

A **statement** is a complete instruction terminated by a `;` (semicolon optional but recommended). Strict mode is enabled with `"use strict";` and disables sloppy features.

<!-- SECTION_1_END -->

