# SECTION 4: Structural Diagrams & Schematics

## 4.1 JavaScript Execution Pipeline (Browser)

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[HTML Document Parsed] --> B[Parser Builds DOM Tree]
    A --> C[CSS Parser Builds CSSOM]
    B --> D[Combine DOM + CSSOM]
    C --> D
    D --> E[Render Tree]
    E --> F[Layout / Reflow]
    F --> G[Paint / Rasterize]
    G --> H[Composite Layers to Screen]
    I[script tag encountered] --> J{Defer / Async?}
    J -- No --> K[Pause HTML Parsing]
    K --> L[JS Engine Fetches and Executes]
    L --> M[Modify DOM or CSSOM]
    M --> F
    J -- Defer --> N[Download in Parallel, Execute Before DOMContentLoaded]
    N --> M
    J -- Async --> O[Download in Parallel, Execute Immediately When Ready]
    O --> M
    style A fill:#FFD700
    style L fill:#FF6347
    style M fill:#90EE90
    style H fill:#87CEEB
```

**Explanation:** When the browser hits a `<script>` tag, by default it **pauses** HTML parsing, downloads the script, and executes it. The `async` and `defer` attributes change this behaviour ‚Äî `defer` waits for full HTML parsing, `async` runs as soon as downloaded.

## 4.2 JavaScript Engine Architecture (V8 Overview)

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A[JS Source Code] --> B[Parser]
    B --> C[AST Abstract Syntax Tree]
    C --> D[Ignition Interpreter]
    D --> E[Bytecode]
    E --> F{TurboFan Optimizing Compiler}
    F -- Hot Function --> G[Optimized Machine Code]
    F -- Deopt Triggered --> H[Deoptimize to Bytecode]
    G --> I[CPU Execution]
    H --> D
    I --> J[Garbage Collector Mark Sweep Compacting]
    style A fill:#FFD700
    style D fill:#FFA07A
    style F fill:#FF6347
    style G fill:#90EE90
    style J fill:#87CEEB
```

**Explanation:** V8 first parses JS to an **AST**, then Ignition interprets it as **bytecode**. Frequently-executed ("hot") functions are JIT-compiled by **TurboFan** to native code. The **Garbage Collector** reclaims heap memory using mark-sweep-compact.

## 4.3 Class Inheritance & Prototype Chain

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    O[Object.prototype] --> A[Animal.prototype]
    A --> D[Dog.prototype]
    D --> I[dogInstance]
    O --> S[Student.prototype]
    S --> G[Graduate.prototype]
