### Q1. Differentiate between `var`, `let`, and `const` in JavaScript. (3 Marks)

**Model Answer:**

| Feature | `var` | `let` | `const` |
|---|---|---|---|
| Scope | Function | Block | Block |
| Hoisting | Hoisted (initialized as `undefined`) | Hoisted (TDZ until declaration) | Hoisted (TDZ until declaration) |
| Re-declaration | Allowed in same scope | Not allowed in same scope | Not allowed in same scope |
| Re-assignment | Allowed | Allowed | **Not allowed** (binding is constant) |
| Introduced | ES1 (1995) | ES6 (2015) | ES6 (2015) |

**Conclusion:** Modern JavaScript prefers `const` by default and `let` only when re-assignment is needed; `var` is legacy and should be avoided. *(3 marks)*

