### Q2. Explain the difference between `==` and `===` operators with an example. (3 Marks)

**Model Answer:**

- `==` (**Abstract Equality**) compares values *after* type coercion.
- `===` (**Strict Equality**) compares both value *and* type ‚Äî no coercion.

**Examples:**

```javascript
console.log(5 == "5");     // true  (string coerced to number)
console.log(5 === "5");    // false (different types)
console.log(null == undefined);   // true  (special rule)
console.log(null === undefined);  // false
```

**Conclusion:** Always prefer `===` to avoid unexpected type-coercion bugs. *(3 marks)*

