## 5.4 Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember (Rapid-Revision Checklist)

> **High-density revision bullets ‚Äî read this section the night before the exam.**

- **JavaScript** = interpreted, dynamically-typed, prototype-based scripting language executed by the browser's JS engine.
- **ECMAScript** is the spec; JavaScript is the implementation.
- Embedding: **inline / internal `<script>` / external `.js`**.
- Variables: `let` (mutable, block), `const` (immutable binding, block), `var` (function, hoisted ‚Äî avoid).
- 8 data types: `number`, `string`, `boolean`, `null`, `undefined`, `bigint`, `symbol`, `object`.
- `typeof null === "object"` ‚Äî historical bug, remember it!
- `prompt()` returns a **string** ‚Äî always `Number()`-convert before arithmetic.
- `alert()` for output, `confirm()` for boolean, `prompt()` for string input.
- Operators precedence: unary > multiplicative > additive > relational > equality > logical > assignment.
- Always prefer `===` over `==`.
- `+` with string ‚Üí concatenation; `-`, `*`, `/` ‚Üí always numeric.
- Decision: `if / else if / else`, ternary `? :`, `switch` (with `break`).
- Loops: `while` (0+), `do-while` (1+), `for` (0+), `for‚Ä¶of` (iterables), `for‚Ä¶in` (object keys).
- Loop control: `break` (exits), `continue` (skips iteration).
- Functions: declaration (hoisted), expression, arrow `(args) => expr`.
- Default params: `function f(x = 10) { }`.
- Rest: `function f(...args) { }`; Spread: `f(...arr)`.
- Arrays are **zero-indexed, heterogeneous, dynamic-length objects**.
- Mutating methods: `push`, `pop`, `shift`, `unshift`, `splice`, `sort`, `reverse`.
- Non-mutating: `slice`, `concat`, `map`, `filter`, `reduce`, `find`, `forEach`.
- Spread `...` copies/merges; destructuring extracts.
- `Math.max(...arr)` and `Math.min(...arr)` for extremes.
- Classes: `class Name { constructor() {} method() {} }` ‚Äî sugar over prototypes.
- `static` methods belong to class, not instance.
- Inheritance: `class Child extends Parent { constructor(){ super(); } }`.
- `super(args)` calls parent constructor; `super.method()` calls parent method.
- Hoisting: `var` ‚Üí initialized `undefined`; `let/const` ‚Üí Temporal Dead Zone (TDZ).
- JavaScript engines: V8 (Chrome/Node), SpiderMonkey (Firefox), JavaScriptCore (Safari).
- Execution: Parse ‚Üí AST ‚Üí Bytecode (Ignition) ‚Üí Optimized Machine Code (TurboFan JIT).
- Garbage Collection: mark-sweep-compact.
- Big-O: array `push`/`pop` ‚Üí $O(1)$; `shift`/`unshift` ‚Üí $O(n)$; `indexOf`/`includes` ‚Üí $O(n)$.
- Best practice: `const` by default, `let` when needed, never `var`.
- `Number.isNaN()` is strict; `isNaN()` coerces ‚Äî prefer strict form.
- Template literals `` `Hello ${name}` `` preferred over `"Hello " + name`.
- Always validate user input ‚Äî never trust `prompt()`.

